---
By: Sivananda
Locus:
  Page: 40
  Verse: 9
Tags:
  - Cause
---
The law of cause and effect is inexorable and unrelenting. You reap a
harvest of suffering, poverty, pain and sorrow, because you have sown the
seed of evil in the past. You reap a harvest of plenty and bliss owing to
your sowing of seeds of good.
